distinctRegions.name: Western Village
distinctRegions.description: A small village located near a body of water, providing a strategic point for resources and defense.

distinctRegions.name: Central Crossroads
distinctRegions.description: The main intersection of roads, offering multiple paths for movement and strategy.

distinctRegions.name: Eastern Castle
distinctRegions.description: A fortified structure providing a defensive stronghold and strategic advantage.

distinctRegions.name: Southern Outpost
distinctRegions.description: A small outpost near the water, serving as a defensive position and lookout point.

chokePoints: Narrow road between walls at (5,0) and (6,0)
strategicConsiderations: The Western Village provides a resource point and is defensible due to its proximity to the lake.
The Central Crossroads is crucial for movement and offers multiple strategic paths.
The Eastern Castle is a strong defensive position with limited access points.
The Southern Outpost serves as a lookout and defensive position, with the armory providing additional resources.
metadata.description: An outdoor map featuring a network of roads connecting various key locations, including villages and a castle. The terrain is a mix of open plains and strategic choke points formed by walls and water.

distinctRegions.name: Castle Entrance
distinctRegions.description: A fortified structure with a grand entrance, surrounded by walls and plains. Provides a defensive position with limited access points.

distinctRegions.name: Central Forest
distinctRegions.description: A dense forest area providing cover and strategic movement options. It is surrounded by plains and cliffs, making it a key area for ambushes and tactical maneuvers.

distinctRegions.name: River Crossing
distinctRegions.description: A river with two wooden bridges allowing passage. This area serves as a critical chokepoint for movement across the map.

distinctRegions.name: Southern Forest
distinctRegions.description: A smaller forested area offering additional cover, surrounded by plains and cliffs. It provides a secondary route for flanking maneuvers.

strategicConsiderations: Defend the Castle Entrance to control access to the map.
Use the Central Forest for ambushes and to control movement.
Control the River Crossing to restrict enemy movement.
Utilize the Southern Forest for flanking and surprise attacks.
metadata.description: A lush outdoor map featuring a castle, dense forests, and a river with bridges.
